results.name: Decimal expansion of the argument of -1 + 2*i.
comment: Gives closed forms for many arctangent values:
arctan(2) = Pi - a, arctan(1/2) = a - Pi/2,
Dihedral angle in the dodecahedron (radians). - _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 24 2012
Larger interior angle (in radians) of a golden rhombus; A105199 is the smaller interior angle. - _Eric W. Weisstein_, Dec 17 2018
link: Rick L. Shepherd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Golden Rhombus
xref: Platonic solids' dihedral angles: A137914 (tetrahedron), A156546 (octahedron), A019669 (cube), A236367 (icosahedron). - _Stanislav Sykora_, Jan 23 2014
Cf. A105199 (smaller interior angle of the golden rhombus).
